The paper focuses on answering web queries using HTML tables, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories in computer science, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Databases (cs.DB), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Among these, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely categories since they deal with NLP and information retrieval, which are central to the paper's approach. However, cs.DB, cs.AI, and cs.LG are also relevant since they involve data management, ML, and deep learning, which are used in the paper's methodology.
